 population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Lumley was born about 1160, in Lumley, Durham, England, United Kingdom, his father, Uchtred Lumley, was 21 and his mother, Algitha of Northumberland, was 31. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Judith Hesilden. He died about 1199, in Chester-le-Street, Durham, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 41."},"et":{"Abt 1160–Abt 1199":"umbes 1160–umbes 1199","1160–1199":"1160–1199","–Male":"Surnud","1160–Female":"1160–Surnud","1182–Female":"1182–Surnud","1190–1280":"1190–1280","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","1130–Female":"1130–Surnud","1190":"1190","about 1182":"umbes 1182","Abt 1199":"umbes 1199","1199":"1199","1130":"1130","1140":"1140","Abt 1160":"umbes 1160","1182":"1182","1160":"1160","1280":"1280","Chester-le-Street, Durham, England, United Kingdom":"Chester-le-Street, Durham, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lumley, Durham, England":"Lumley, Durham, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1160–Abt 1199":"noin 1160–noin 1199","1160–1199":"1160–1199","–Male":"Kuollut","1160–Female":"1160–Kuollut","1182–Female":"1182–Kuollut","1190–1280":"1190–1280","1140–Male":"1140–Kuollut","1130–Female":"1130–Kuollut","1190":"1190","about 1182":"noin 1182","Abt 1199":"noin 1199","1199":"1199","1130":"1130","1140":"1140","Abt 1160":"noin 1160","1182":"1182","1160":"1160","1280":"1280","Chester-le-Street, Durham, England, United Kingdom":"Chester-le-Street, Durham, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Lumley, Durham, England":"Lumley, Durham, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1160–Abt 1199":"environ 1160–environ 1199","1160–1199":"1160–1199","–Male":"Décédé","1160–Female":"1160–Décédée","1182–Female":"1182–Décédée","1190–1280":"1190–1280","1140–Male